Date: Fri, 5 Dec 2008 00:43:25 +0530
From: "K.Prasad" <>
Subject: [RFC Patch 5/9] Use wrapper routines around debug registers in processor related functions
Sender: linux-kernel-owner@vger.kernel.org
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <linux-kernel.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org
X-Lkml-Link: https://lkml.org/lkml/2008/12/4/321

This patch enables the use of wrapper routines to access the debug/breakpoint
registers.
Signed-off-by: K.Prasad <prasad@linux.vnet.ibm.com>
Signed-off-by: Alan Stern <stern@rowland.harvard.edu>
---
